    About this item

    • Ultra-Soft Stretch Fabric: Crafted from ultra-soft, natural stretch fabric, this durable scrub set ensures comfort and flexibility, perfect for long hours in healthcare settings.
    • Y-Neck Wrap Top with Contrasting Binding: The Y-neck wrap top features stylish contrasting binding, adding a touch of flair to your professional attire. The fitted back and waistband create a slim, flattering look.
    • Functional and Comfortable Design: The top includes a tagless neck for added comfort, equipped with two roomy patch pockets and two extra pockets on both sides.The pants have an elastic closure with an adjustable drawstring, straight cut, and multiple cargo pockets.
    • Practical for Healthcare Professionals: Ideal for nurses, dental assistants, medical and nursing students, doctors, and hospital workers, this scrub set combines elegance with practicality to meet the needs of healthcare professionals.
    • Easy Care: Designed for your convenience, this womens scrub set is machine washable, ensuring easy care and maintenance.

    How customer reviews and ratings work

    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    Customers say

    Customers find the medical scrub set comfortable with soft material and a flattering style that looks good on women's bodies. The material is medium thickness, durable, and stretchy, offering good value for money. The fit receives mixed feedback - while some say it runs big on top, others note it's a bit snug in the thighs. The color quality also gets mixed reviews, with some saying it doesn't fade while others report it bleeding onto other clothing.

    4 out of 5 stars
    Decent
    Fabric: surprisingly soft and has 2 way stretch (left to right), doesn't have up and down stretch. Moderate thickness. The navy color is a very dark navy.Fit : I'm 5"7 and 205 lbs. I like the length of the scrub top. Covers my backside and stomach completely. Pants are high rise in my opinion, which I like. The scrub pants are basically a tapered leg, which isn't my favorite. They are a smidgen long on me but only because they are tapered, so they run into the tops of my sneakers. I prefer a straight leg or a slight flaired leg that flows. I put on a white low top shoe in the picture below so you can see how it the scrubs look against whiteOverall: for the price, these are a nice set. Not my absolute favorite but a decent buy that I will definitely use. I feel they are true to size. I ordered an XXL mainly for my waist and hips. I'm a 16 in most department stores. These are just a touch loose but if I went down to XL they might be too tight.

      3.0 out of 5 stars Good flex, decent fit, so-so finish
      Reviewed in the United States on April 21, 2016
      Size: MediumColor: BlackVerified Purchase
      Purchased for my wife, she is a veterinary assistant. She was looking for something flexible enough yet strong enough to deal with squirming big dogs. Overall she was very happy with the flex and feel of the material, but she felt they ran slightly small. She prefers these over the scrubs given by her work, (Saturday is "casual"/wear your non work issued scrubs day) but not as much as her Grey's Anatomy scrubs.
      The only issue she had with them is the seam on the right toro was not lined up correctly when sewn and the stitch missed the fabric on one side. There was about 4 inches of open seam. This was fixed with a quick re-stitch, unfortunately she didn't notice until after she was at work. Aside for the missed stitch I felt they were a good combination of quality and price.
